    <thetext>Description of problem:
The ncurses shipped with f25 has a bug that causes it to buffer even when the output sequence contains some delay:

% strace tput flash
...
nanosleep({tv_sec=0, tv_nsec=100000000}, 0xbf96d3e4) = 0
write(1, &quot;\33[?5h\33[?5l&quot;, 10)          = 10
exit_group(0)                           = ?
+++ exited with 0 +++

(the sleep should be after \33[?5h and then another write).

This is a known bug that has been fixed in more recent versions (http://invisible-island.net/ncurses/NEWS.html#t20161217). Please upgrade this broken ncurses version in f25.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
ncurses-6.0-6.20160709.fc25.i686

How reproducible:
always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. tput flash

Actual results:
nothing

Expected results:
screen flashes</thetext>
